{
  "texts": [
    "However, some co-relevance matrices can be sparse where large partitions of it contain zero co-relevance.",
    "Consequently, techniques emerged to reduce computational cost and memory requirements to process sparse co-relevance matrices by focusing computations only on submatrices that have co-relevance (Child et al. 2019).",
    "The GPT-3 architecture differs slightly from the previous version in that the decoder layers alternated between dense and sparse co-relevance matrix factorization (Brown et al. 2020).",
    "The factorization technique splits the original co-relevance matrix into smaller sub-matrices that have proportionally less non-zero elements.",
    "Hence, factorized matrices will operate on nearby tokens that have stronger co-relevance."
  ]
}